Hi Team,

We are implementing a High-Risk Transaction (HRT) step-up authentication POC using PingOne AIC + PingGateway 2026.3, replacing Transmit Security.

— WHAT WE ARE DOING —

1. Browser invokes HRTStepUpJourney via Authorization Code + PKCE:
   /oauth2/authorize?authIndexType=service&authIndexValue=HRTStepUpJourney&login_hint=<xsmid>&state=<xsmid>

2. After authentication, a Scripted Decision node (StoreXsmid) runs:
   - Reads xsmid from requestParameters.get('login_hint')
   - Calls session.setProperty('xsmid', xsmid)
   - Calls transientState.put('xsmid', xsmid)

3. AIC issues id_token via OIDC Claims Script (HRTOIDCClaimsScript):
   - Script Type: OIDC Claims
   - xsmid mapped to profile scope
   - Resolver: session.getProperty('xsmid')

4. PingGateway receives JWT + xsmid from client, introspects JWT with AIC, matches xsmid claim in JWT with xsmid in request.

— WHAT IS CONFIRMED WORKING —

✅ Full Authorization Code + PKCE flow completes
✅ OIDC Claims Script runs (hardcoded value appears in JWT)
✅ StoreXsmid script runs without errors
✅ xsmid is bound to JWT via s_hash (SHA256 of state)

— WHAT IS FAILING —

❌ session.getProperty('xsmid') returns null in OIDC Claims Script
❌ xsmid claim not appearing in id_token

— AIC CONFIGURATION DONE —

• Session Property Whitelist Service: xsmid added
• OAuth2 Provider Persistent Claims: xsmid added
• OAuth2 Provider Supported Claims: xsmid added
• Always Return Claims in ID Token: ON
• Enable OAuth2 Provider Overrides on client: ON

— QUESTIONS —

1. Does session.setProperty() in a Scripted Decision node persist to the OIDC Claims Script at token issuance time? If not, what is the correct way?

2. What is the correct expression syntax for the Set Session Properties node to read a value from sharedState? (${sharedState['xsmid']} stored a literal string for us)

3. What is the Ping-recommended approach to pass a custom transaction ID from the authorize request (login_hint/state) into the id_token as a plain claim?
